When to apply: Any code change or bug fix. What to do: Write/adjust tests and keep coverage meaningful.

- Runner: Use Jest (`pnpm test`). Config in `jest.config.js`, setup in `jest.setup.js` (jsdom, mocks).
- Placement: Co-locate tests under `__tests__` or `*.test.ts(x)` next to code.
- Types of tests:
  - Unit: components, hooks, use cases. Mock network with `whatwg-fetch`/MSW (when added).
  - Integration: Next.js route handlers in `app/api/**` with mocked deps.
- Snapshots: Keep snapshots small and stable. Prefer explicit assertions over large snapshots.
- Fixtures/mocks: Use Testing Library patterns. Avoid deep mocking—test behavior over implementation details.
- Coverage: Maintain or improve current coverage; do not remove meaningful tests without replacement.
- Performance: Tests must run fast locally and in CI. Prefer deterministic tests; avoid real sleeps/network.
- Preflight: Lint and typecheck must be green alongside tests.
- Documentation: Update `docs/Testing.md` when conventions or helpers change.

